  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I don't want to be confused by messing up a password and signing phrase.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Improvement\r\n\r\nCurrent problems with the signing phrase popup are:\r\n\r\n1. Confusing UI. This came up from UXR sessions: users tried to type signing phrase into the password field. \r\n2. Tied to a specific layout. Confirmation and cancel buttons currently take place outside popup that triggered a problem with the implementation of this popup for different use cases (sign a message to login into Dapp, also it could be used in the `paid master node` feature)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n![slice](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6559881/39766860-99c96ede-52e5-11e8-8be9-9f60c5863937.jpg)\r\n\r\nMockups in Zeplin â€” https://app.zeplin.io/project/5a55d587ba304eed4d2c942f?seid=5af2c256e817e05b24908352\r\n(provide your email to be added to a Zeplin project) \r\n\r\nPrototype with logic and animations \r\nhttps://www.dropbox.com/s/kbkpjiw8xw23cv5/17_signing%20phrase%20popup.mov?dl=0\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6559881/39766847-907e7b76-52e5-11e8-9946-38a03e1d9b56.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Send transaction\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Android|iOS\r\n",
